statement:
A collection $\mathcal{A}$ of subsets of $X$ is an \emph{algebra of sets}
(or \emph{Boolean algebra of sets}, or \emph{field of sets}) if:
- [label=(\roman*)]
- $X \in \mathcal{A}$;
- $A \in \mathcal{A}$ implies $A^c = X \setminus A \in \mathcal{A}$;
- $A, B \in \mathcal{A}$ implies $A \cup B \in \mathcal{A}$.
